Table I contains a list of variable definitions, and Table II presents descriptive statistics for the sample. 4.1 MEASURES OF SCALE ECONOMIES Large cable operators have lower costs than small cable operators for reasons other than bargaining power. Several studies have found empirical evidence of scale economies in cable television. To measure the effect of size on bargaining power, it is necessary to account for the effect of size on scale economies.
